  One of the problems I see with the stolen car parts is that in the old
days you would see Joe Blow at a swap with a pile of parts off of 1 year of
car. Now it seems it's a lot of the perminate swap guys that are fencing the
stolen parts at the swaps because they have piles of used stuff. That is one
of the reasons I don't sell much used stuff at the swaps and am careful of
who I buy stuff from.
  A good example was we were at a swap and 2 different people found stolen
parts off of there own car at the same vendors spot. I guy had 2 deck lids
stolen and the other had an EMPI steering wheel stolen, both from different
areas, yet the same vendor had them for sale.
  As for Jon and Rachael's 67 bug, I'm sure we'll see parts off it at Pomona
in a couple weeks. I didn't see anything at the Copperstate that looked like
they may have come off of it.

Ronnie   cut off the thieves right hand and watch them try to wipe there a#(-at-)
   


